            "commit": "e5f630a54404e69102d48fa28b44ee3aa5e133f6",
            "subject": "LU-8050 osp: not use obdo::o_lcookie for non-onwire RPC data"
          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Fan Yong",
          "email": "fan.yong@intel.com",
          "date": "2016-11-20 09:22:46.000000000",
          "tz": 480
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Bobi Jam",
          "email": "bobijam.xu@intel.com",
          "date": "2017-04-05 10:17:15.000000000",
          "tz": 480
        },
        "subject": "LU-8054 lfsck: enhance lfsck notify API",
        "message": "LU-8054 lfsck: enhance lfsck notify API\n\nOriginally, the lfsck_in_notify() contains too much functionalities,\nincluding both the remote LFSCK control and local LFSCK notification.\nThese LFSCK requirements/callers share the structure \"lfsck_request\"\nto transfer kinds of data, as to it is very difficult to enhance the\n\"lfsck_request\" for more local LFSCK requirements. Because enlarging\nor adjusting the \"lfsck_request\" fields will affect the LFSCK RPC on\nwire protocol and cause interoperability issues.\n\nThe patch splits the local LFSCK notifications from lfsck_in_notify(),\nand introduce new LFSCK API lfsck_in_notify_local() for them. Then\neven if we have more local LFSCK requirements in the future, we can\nenhance such API freely without affecting LFSCK RPC protocol.\n\nReviewed-on: https://review.whamcloud.com/24881\n\nSigned-off-by: Fan Yong <fan.yong@intel.com>\nChange-Id: I8f285c6680de66a73050e167dc3874a4f6bf4ad0\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
